From f74353e84b0b9bb06d98a0d840832edd7971a9e1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 18:59:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: bug fixes and UI/UX improvements for dashboard and scan
 jobs

Backend:
- Fix 422 when adding a vendor without a driver (VendorSchema.driver now Optional)
- Don't delete still-running subnet scan jobs during stale cleanup (long scans on
  large subnets would vanish mid-scan and the UI polling got 404)
- Report subnet scan progress while pinging hosts so the progress bar moves

Frontend:
- Escape HTML in all dynamically rendered values (hostnames from device configs,
  group/vendor names, EUVD API descriptions) to prevent broken markup and stored XSS
- Use data attributes instead of inline string interpolation for delete/add/analyze
  handlers (names with quotes no longer break onclick)
- Highlight the correct tab button when switchTab is called programmatically
  (e.g. after CSV import)
- Re-render vendor table on language switch
- Reset group filters to "all" when the previously selected group was deleted
- Submit login, setup wizard, group creation and subnet scan with the Enter key
- Close modals by clicking the backdrop; Escape closes the subnet scan modal
  (kept out of the CLI modal so Escape still reaches the SSH terminal)
- Empty-state message in the device table instead of a bare header
- Responsive layout: sidebar stacks above content below 1000px
- Fix btn-primary hover color (teal leftover on blue button)

https://claude.ai/code/session_016LrhmUxHWiKHnhkrWHFTtM
